# Source: 5-whys (4 ideas → 2 questions, 2 skipped)
{"question": "is 5 whys a good method for investigating production incidents?", "ground_truth": "The 5 whys method traces a single causal chain by asking 'why' repeatedly. It originated from Toyota and Taiichi Ohno's production system. It works for simple problems but actively discourages comprehensive investigation of complex ones — each 'why' narrows focus to one path, abandoning alternative perspectives."}
{"question": "how to investigate a bug that seems to have multiple causes?", "ground_truth": "Complex problems have multiple interacting causes, not a single root cause. Methods like 5 whys pick one chain and miss the others. Analyze from multiple perspectives instead of following just one chain of 'why' questions."}
