# Source: acceptance-criteria (4 ideas → 4 questions)
{"question": "what's the difference between acceptance criteria and definition of done?", "ground_truth": "Acceptance criteria are predefined conditions a product must fulfill to be accepted by customers and users. They are specific to a user story, unlike Definition of Done which applies universally to all tasks."}
{"question": "how should we write acceptance criteria?", "ground_truth": "There are two formats for writing acceptance criteria: scenario-oriented (Given/When/Then) and rule-oriented (checklist). Given/When/Then works best for user flows, while checklists suit system-level or design requirements."}
