{"question": "what's the difference between ad hoc testing and exploratory testing?", "ground_truth": "Ad hoc testing is unstructured with no defined goals. Exploratory testing is structured, time-boxed, and session-based with documentation. Ad hoc testing provides maximum value after formal testing concludes but should never replace formal testing."}
